      <section eId="sec_CHC-424-3">
        <num>CHC 424.3</num>
        <heading>424.3. Â CASA; duties</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-424-3__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Provide independent, factual information to the court regarding the children and cases to which they are assigned.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-424-3__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Advocate on behalf of the children involved in the cases in which they are assigned what they perceive to be in the best interest of the children.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-424-3__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Monitor proceedings in cases in which they have been assigned and advise and assist the court in its determination of the best interest of the children involved.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73166</p>
